    <%# <h3>GOALS & OBJECTIVES</h3>
    <p>To help young Chinese filmmakers develop authentic voices; to support less-known Chinese filmmakers with access to an international audience; to provide all filmmakers opportunities for networking through the platform of our festival.</p>
    <p>To create alternative cinematic encounters for audiences across the spectrum from feature films to documentary forms and artistic experiments; to offer unique festival experiences through a rich array of spoken-word events, audience discussions and expert panels; to provide an open and friendly platform for meeting like-minded people and taking a break from routine.</p>
    <p>To enrich the diversity of art institutions and cinemas’ exhibitions and activities; to facilitate art institutions and cinemas reaching out to heterogeneous audiences; to integrate bottom-up artistic powers from different organisations and sectors and to build a sustainably cooperative partnership.</p>
    <p>To increase the visibility of the Chinese community in Berlin and other regions as well as to enhance inclusion, openness and cohesion of the city; to contribute to the artistic and cultural diversity of the local community and the city and to improve the innovative film climate from local to global.</p> %>
